<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-53-0434 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author formulates, with the dim light of the future presently available,a blueprint for natural gas ratemaking in the 1980's. He believes thatboth the Natural Gas Act and the Natural Gas Policy Act (NGPA) imposeupon pipelines a prudence standard applicable to pipeline operations,not only for purposes of formulating rates, but for purposes of recoveringpurchase gas costs, as well.</TEXT></DOC>